> Perhaps something like
> 
> ```cs
> x = target.Members[_stringValue];
> if(x is null && _stringValue.EndsWith("String"))
> {
>     var nonStringName = _stringValue.Replace("String", String.Empty);
>     x = target.Members[nonStringName]?.Value.ToString();
> }
> ```

We could avoid allocations with switch expression:
```c#
var propertyName =  _stringValue switch
{
    "NameString"               => "Name",
    "LengthString"             => "Length",
    "LastWriteTimeString" => "LastWriteTime",
    _ => string.Empty
}
```
